text.section:
Before issuing any shares of a class or series created under this section, the corporation shall deliver to the Secretary of State for filing articles of amendment, which are effective without shareholder action, that set forth:
The name of the corporation;
The text of the amendment determining the terms of the class or series of shares;
The date it was adopted; and
A statement that the amendment was duly adopted by the board of directors.

The board of directors may adopt articles of amendment without shareholder action to make any of the following changes to a class or series created under this section:
Increase the number of shares of a series but not above the total number of authorized and unissued shares of the class;
Decrease the number of shares of a series but not below the number of shares of the series then issued and outstanding;
Amend the designation, preferences, limitations, or relative rights of the shares of a class or series if no shares of the class or series are then issued or outstanding; or
Eliminate the designation of, and all references to, a series from the articles of incorporation if no shares of the series are then issued and outstanding.

Articles of amendment adopted pursuant to subsection (5) of this section shall be delivered to the Secretary of State for filing and shall state:
The name of the corporation;
The designation of the class or series subject to the amendment;
The text of the amendment changing the class or series;
The date the amendment was adopted; and
A statement that the amendment was duly adopted by the board of directors.
